8 PROPOSED SUBCOMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to Medicaid; authorizing flexible
payment structures for prenatal, delivery, and
10 postpartum care; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4013 of Title 56, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. The Oklahoma Medicaid Program shall reimburse for prenatal,
19 delivery, and postpartum services separately in lieu of a global
20 payment or an all-inclusive payment methodology for maternity
21 services.
22 B. Prenatal, delivery, and postpartum services include without
23 limitation:
24 1. Office visits;
Req. No. 16396 Page 1

1 2. Laboratory fees;
2 3. Physician-ordered testing;
3 4. Blood work;
4 5. Fetal nonstress tests; and
5 6. Continuous glucose monitors or other services for
6 gestational diabetes, when medically necessary.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
